    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators propose to characterize MPs in aHUS and TTP both at the onset and
      throughout treatment. The investigators believe that the number, size, and cell origin of MPs
      will differ between these two diseases. The hypothesis is that endothelial derived MPs will
      be higher in number and comprise a larger portion of the MP population in aHUS and that
      platelet MPs will comprise a larger number and greater proportion of MPs in TTP. The
      investigators believe that MP identity and number can be used to reliably differentiate
      between aHUS and TTP at disease onset.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
